      <section eId="sec_82_06">
        <num>82.06</num>
        <heading>Formation and term of agreement</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_82_06__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>An adult may enter into a supported decision-making agreement at\nany time if the adult enters into the agreement voluntarily.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_82_06__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A decision-maker may sign a supported decision-making agreement in\nany manner, including electronic signatures permitted under article\nthree of the state technology law.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_82_06__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A supported decision-making agreement formed under the provisions\nof this article shall remain in effect unless and until revoked by the\ndecision-maker.\n  * NB Effective 90 days from the date that the regulations issued in\naccordance with ยง 1 of chapter 481 of 2022 appear in the New York State\nRegister or the date such regulations are adopted, whichever is later.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
